    "description_XXX": "Amon, mentioned in Jeremiah 46:25 and Nam.3.8, refers to the Egyptian god Amon and the city of Thebes, respectively.",
    "description_XXXX": "Amon appears in two different contexts in the Bible. In Jeremiah 46:25, Amon refers to the Egyptian god, who was one of the most important deities in ancient Egypt. Amon was often combined with the sun god Ra to form the deity Amon-Ra, the king of the gods. The prophecy in Jeremiah 46 foretells the punishment of Egypt and its gods, including Amon. <p>In Nam.3.8, Amon is mentioned as a city, which is most likely a reference to Thebes, the ancient capital of Egypt. Thebes was known as \"No-Amon,\" meaning \"the city of Amon,\" due to the prominence of the god Amon in the city. Nahum compares the fate of Nineveh to that of Thebes, which had been conquered and destroyed despite its power and the protection of its god.",
